args: I'm glad I brought you with me, Felicia.
I didn't think we would end up\nwith this many groceries.
Neither did I—but the shopkeeper\ngave us so much extra food.
Everyone is going to be surprised\nwhen they see it all.
Cleo's head may explode\nwith the possibilities.
And Ranzal and Luca will be happy\nfor very different reasons.
Then Elisanne will warn them both\nnot to eat too much.
Mym will ask what dish you like most so\nshe can make it for you.

Meanwhile, Notte will beg Cleo to make
another cupcake-marshmallow pizza—
which is a thing I did not know existed
until about a week ago.
Ha! We'd better get back soon\nso we can...
I see them. Let's hide behind the trees.
Yes, sir. We can move out as soon\nas we have cover of night.
They look like imperial soldiers.\nWhat are they doing here?
There's a whole unit of them.
Well, the two of us certainly can't take\nthem all on. Let's sneak past, then\ninform the others what we've—
Stay alert, men! As soon as the sun sets,\nwe move on the traitorous prince's castle!
We don't have time for a detour.\nI'm going in.
I know, but I have an idea.\nWhat do you think about...
Now YOU have a death wish!
But it's a much better chance than you\ntaking on an entire legion alone.
You all saved me—it's my turn to help.
...All right. I'll leave this to you.
Can't say I'm too happy about\ndoing this at night.
Naw, I'd stab a man in the back and sleep\nlike a baby. But being in a forest at night?\nCan't help but feel it's full of... Y'know.
Haw haw haw! Don't be a sap!
Ghosts are just a way for cowards to\npretend they—Hey! Who goes there?!
A sylvan girl? Who are you? Speak!
Commander?! What happened?!\nAnd where's that woman?!
There she is! Hey, you! Were you the\none who attacked our commander?!
You won't distract us again! Take this!
H-hey! You okay?!\n...Hell, she's gone again!
Don't look! If you look,\nyou'll be kill—AAAARGH!
Run before it kills us all! RUUUUN!
Whew! I was on edge the whole time,\nbut your plan worked perfectly.
I mean, it was dynamite on paper,\nbut so many things could have\ngone terribly wrong.
And that would have put you\nin serious danger.
I'm sorry. This is all my fault.\nIt was my plan, after all.
I didn't mean to cause trouble.
Felicia, you SAVED us. I'd never have\nbeen able to take out all those soldiers\nwithout you here.
Of course—but I was more concerned\nabout the Halidom and everyone in it.
I've already lost one home—\nI couldn't bear to lose another.
Besides, I had you with me.
That's right. You give me courage.
If I was still how I used to be, I would\nhave been too scared to do anything.
But having you by my side gives me\nthe courage to confront what I must.
That's...kind of embarrassing to\nhave said straight to your face.
But I think you're giving me too much\ncredit—YOU'RE the one who's stronger,\ncompletely independent of me.
I do. After all, you're the one who\nsaved us back there with your dance.
I'm going to keep doing all I can\nto protect everyone.
The Halidom is my second home now.
I'm happy to hear you say that.
Then shall we make our way back?\nEveryone must be waiting.
